The government has contradicted its earlier statement on the ban of maize from its Newbrough's Uganda and Tanzania over what it termed as high aflatoxin levels in maize being imported from those countries. according to the cabinet secretary ministry of agriculture peter many, the government has not banned importation of maize from its neighbours, it has just tightened rules and regulations on the safety of food coming into the country, and that any consignment that meets laid down safety requirement will be allowed in.